Vertebrata }} 'Craniata' (sometimes 'Craniota') is a proposed clade of chordate animals that contains the Myxini (hagfish), Petromyzontida (including lampreys), and Gnathostomata (jawed vertebrates)Campbell & Reece 2005 p. 676Cracraft & Donoghue 2004 p. 390 as living representatives. As the name suggests, Craniata are animals with a (hard bone or cartilage) skull in Chordata.
